### Define a Text Field in Payload Collection Config

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/overview.mdx

This example shows how to define a simple 'text' field within a Payload Collection configuration. The `fields` array contains an object for each field, specifying its `name` and `type` properties. This field will store a string value in the database and be rendered as a text input in the Admin Panel.

```ts
import type { CollectionConfig } from 'payload'

export const Page: CollectionConfig = {
  slug: 'pages',
  // highlight-start
  fields: [
    {
      name: 'field',
      type: 'text',
    },
  ],
  // highlight-end
}
```

