### Augment PayloadCMS Types for Plugin-Specific Field Properties (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/PLUGIN-DEVELOPMENT.md

This snippet demonstrates how to extend Payload's core types using module augmentation, specifically `FieldCustom`, to add plugin-specific properties to fields. This allows developers to define custom metadata and functions (e.g., `toCSV`, `fromCSV` for an import/export plugin) directly on field definitions with full TypeScript support.

```ts
// In plugin types file
declare module 'payload' {
  export interface FieldCustom {
    'plugin-import-export'?: {
      disabled?: boolean
      toCSV?: (value: any) => string
      fromCSV?: (value: string) => any
    }
  }
}

// Usage with TypeScript support
{
  name: 'price',
  type: 'number',
  custom: {
    'plugin-import-export': {
      toCSV: (value) => `$${value.toFixed(2)}`,
      fromCSV: (value) => parseFloat(value.replace('$', '')),
    },
  },
}
```

